Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @sugar snap peas{150%g}.

Place a pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, stir-fry the pepper until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reduce the heat of the pan to medium-high.

Add the @turkey mince{250%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Turkey is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the turkey is browned, add the sugar snaps and garlic to the pan and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @teriyaki sauce{2%sachets}, @hoisin sauce{1%sachet} and @water{50%ml}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the sauce is a little dry.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if needed.

Carefully separate the @udon noodles{300%g} with your hands.

Gently toss them through the sauce.

Cook until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Share the teriyaki turkey noodles between bowls.